SIMPLE: light-o-love
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Light-o-love
<hw>Light"-o'-love`</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧t"⟦osl⟧-l⟦ucr⟧v`)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An old tune of a dance, the name of which
made it a proverbial expression of levity, especially in love
matters.</def> <au>Nares.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Best sing it to the tune of
<xex>light-o'-love</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence: A light or wanton woman; a woman inconstant
in love. Called also <altname>light-of-love</altname>.</def>
<rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lightroom</ent>⟦br⟧
